  "title": "Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></p><p>A <strong>Site Supervisor</strong> is responsible for overseeing and managing daily activities at the construction site to ensure work is carried out safely, efficiently, and in accordance with project requirements. Key duties include:</p><ol><li><p>Monitor the productivity and performance of workers to ensure targets and quality standards are met.</p></li><li><p>Provide technical and engineering support at the work site when required.</p></li><li><p>Prepare daily progress reports and update management on site activities.</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper housekeeping and maintain a clean, safe working environment.</p></li><li><p>Arrange and coordinate materials, tools, and equipment for site operations.</p></li><li><p>Follow instructions and directions issued by the office and management team</p></li></ol>",
